.START 

Regarding your Sept. 5 article "Real Estate Gems in the Texas Rough." The rebound in Texas apartment prices was entirely predictable last year, using the "Wrecking Ball Indicator." Houston newspapers reported the booming business for demolition firms hired by troubled thrifts. 

The thrifts were having foreclosed apartments demolished because they couldn't afford the real-estate taxes on improved property but could carry the taxes on unimproved property. 

Mark Alan Forney 

Englewood N.J. 

